Info.Description:
The number of bits of the color component. The number of colors represented by its value is: 
1: two-color;
2: 4-color;&#xA ;4: 16 colors;
8 or 16: 256 or more colors.

The type represented by the value is as follows: 
Type0: a composite font that can be composed of multiple sub-fonts; 
Type1: a font made with PostScript Type 1 technology ;
MMType1: Multiple Master Type1 font;
Type3: Font containing PDF graphics operators;
TrueType: Fonts made with True Type technology; 
CIDFontType0: Character identification fonts made with Type 1 technology (CID Font); 
CIDFontType2: Character identification made with True Type technology Font.
Character ID Font is usually a font library composed of a large number of characters, such as Chinese characters. When outputting the content of a PDF document, output commands such as TJ specify the output character with a character ID value. Character ID is usually not Unicode value, if you need to extract the text output by the text output command, you need to use the conversion table of the ToUnicode item to convert the character identifier to the character represented by Unicode.

Sets the text rendering method (initial value is 0). Available modes are: 
0: Fill; 1: Stroke Outline; 2: Stroke Outline; 3: No Display (Invisible) );
4: Fill and add patterns; 5: Stroke and add patterns; 6: Stroke solid characters and add patterns; 7: Add patterns to invisible characters
